OL,6,FOn his 17th birthday though, when he
OL,7,Fwas old enough, Roland's dad could no
OL,8,Flonger object, so he signed up as a
OL,9,FRoyal Marine.
OL,11,FQuickly, Roland - known as Ron to his
OL,12,Ffamily - was singled out to become a
OL,13,Fcommando, joining an intelligence unit
OL,14,Fthat was under the command of Ian
OL,15,FFleming, the man who would go on to
OL,16,Fpen the famous James Bond novels.
OL,18,FUnder his charge, he risked his life
OL,19,Ffor Britain's freedom, including
OL,20,Fduring the D-Day operation in June
OL,21,F1944.
